772
00:55:01.190 --> 00:55:02.715
<i>"and for what we believe."</i>

773
00:55:06.870 --> 00:55:09.316
<i>But today, Jimmie,</i>

774
00:55:09.390 --> 00:55:13.076
<i>we're doing the living
and you've done the dying, dear brother.</i>


775
00:55:14.150 --> 00:55:18.314
<i>We will not let your sacrifice
pass in vain, dear brother.</i>


776
00:55:18.390 --> 00:55:20.358
<i>We will not let it go!</i>

777
00:55:20.430 --> 00:55:22.637
<i>We will finish what you were after!</i>

778
00:55:22.710 --> 00:55:25.156
<i>We will get what you were denied!</i>

779
00:55:25.230 --> 00:55:28.757
<i>We will vote and we will
put these men out of office!</i>


780
00:55:28.830 --> 00:55:30.832
<i>We will take their power!</i>

781
00:55:30.910 --> 00:55:33.231
<i>We will win
what you were slaughtered for!</i>


782
00:55:33.430 --> 00:55:35.398
Yeah!

783
00:55:38.150 --> 00:55:40.437
<i>We're going back to Washington.</i>

784
00:55:41.070 --> 00:55:43.118
<i>We're going to demand
to see the President.</i>


785
00:55:43.190 --> 00:55:45.318
<i>And I'm gonna tell him</i>

786
00:55:45.470 --> 00:55:48.679
<i>that Jimmie was murdered
by an administration</i>


787
00:55:48.750 --> 00:55:51.674
<i>that spends millions of dollars every day</i>

788
00:55:51.750 --> 00:55:55.118
<i>to sacrifice life
in the name of liberty in Vietnam,</i>


789
00:55:55.190 --> 00:55:58.160
<i>yet lacks the moral will
and the moral courage</i>


790
00:55:58.230 --> 00:56:02.952
<i>to defend the lives
of its own people here in America!</i>


791
00:56:04.590 --> 00:56:06.433
<i>We will not let it go!</i>

792
00:56:07.590 --> 00:56:11.436
<i>And if he does not act, we will act.
We will act!</i>


793
00:56:11.550 --> 00:56:13.837
<i>We will do it for
all of our lost ones.</i>

794
00:56:13.950 --> 00:56:16.271
<i>All of those, like Jimmie Lee Jackson,</i>

795
00:56:16.350 --> 00:56:20.116
<i>who have gone too soon, taken by hate!</i>

796
00:56:28.190 --> 00:56:29.874
Let me hear the top-tier issues

797
00:56:29.950 --> 00:56:33.875
that have to be evident
in the overall legislation we demand.


798
00:56:33.950 --> 00:56:35.111
Let's break it down.

799
00:56:35.190 --> 00:56:37.636
But let's root this discussion
in what we know.


800
00:56:38.430 --> 00:56:41.001
We know Johnson
can't see the full picture.


801
00:56:41.070 --> 00:56:42.799
So, let's paint it for him.

802
00:56:42.910 --> 00:56:46.995
What are the specific hardships
and humiliations


803
00:56:47.070 --> 00:56:50.995
we can address
within the larger context of legislation?


804
00:56:52.470 --> 00:56:55.553
Doc, we gotta start
with banning these laws that


