00:57:19.510 --> 00:57:22.195
Now, what the hell is that?
Who got that kind of money?


815
00:57:23.870 --> 00:57:25.599
Come on now! Listen now!

816
00:57:25.670 --> 00:57:28.276
The big issue is voting vouchers.

817
00:57:28.350 --> 00:57:29.431
Is that the number one issue?

818
00:57:29.510 --> 00:57:30.591
Now hold on. Let me finish.

819
00:57:30.670 --> 00:57:32.240
'Cause everybody'll forget
about this part.


820
00:57:32.310 --> 00:57:35.120
But if you're Negro,
the only way you can vote


821
00:57:35.190 --> 00:57:37.796
is if an approved registered
voter vouches for you.


822
00:57:37.870 --> 00:57:40.999
Right? So, let's say, you take
some place like Lowndes County,


823
00:57:41.230 --> 00:57:43.232
where there are no Negroes
who are registered


824
00:57:43.310 --> 00:57:45.278
and you've got to have
someone who is registered


825
00:57:45.350 --> 00:57:47.114
to vouch for you.

826
00:57:47.190 --> 00:57:48.396
What are you supposed to do?

827
00:57:49.870 --> 00:57:51.474
Nobody you know,

828
00:57:51.550 --> 00:57:55.794
not a single black person
for 100 miles is registered.


829
00:57:55.870 --> 00:57:59.397
So how do you get the voucher, right?

830
00:57:59.470 --> 00:58:01.837
To get you into the courthouse door

831
00:58:01.910 --> 00:58:04.311
to pay the poll tax

832
00:58:04.390 --> 00:58:06.711
to get your name published

833
00:58:07.110 --> 00:58:08.350
and get yourself dead.

834
00:58:09.910 --> 00:58:10.911
That's true.

835
00:58:10.990 --> 00:58:12.515
We need a new plan!

836
00:58:12.590 --> 00:58:14.194
I can't take him back to Washington

837
00:58:14.270 --> 00:58:17.035
and waltz into the White House
with a list of empty demands.


838
00:58:17.150 --> 00:58:19.039
Tactics, my friends!

839
00:58:19.110 --> 00:58:21.761
We must break down this institution

840
00:58:21.830 --> 00:58:24.720
into the tangible tactics
that it takes to dismantle it.


841
00:58:27.110 --> 00:58:28.157
<i>What's your next move?</i>

842
00:58:28.230 --> 00:58:32.440
A march from Selma to Montgomery
to protest and amplify.


843
00:58:32.590 --> 00:58:34.558
Well, I'll be damned.

844
00:58:34.630 --> 00:58:37.031
This was always part of the plan,
wasn't it?


845
00:58:37.110 --> 00:58:40.034
Provoke some tragedy
in little old Selma, then go big.


846
00:58:40.590 --> 00:58:44.037
Get someone killed
and march on the State Capitol!


847
00:58:44.430 --> 00:58:47.115
Selma to Montgomery's
gotta be 50 miles!


848
00:58:47.190 --> 00:58:49.921
You march those people
into rural Alabama unprotected,


849
00:58:49.990 --> 00:58:51.151
it's gonna be open season.

850
00:58:51.230 --> 00:58:53.676
It's too damn far
and too damn dangerous!


851
00:58:53.790 --> 00:58:55.633
Then propose new legislation, sir.

852
00:58:55.750 --> 00:58:58.321
I can't do that this year. I won't!
I told you.


853
00:58:58.870 --> 00:59:00.872
We need your involvement here,
Mr. President.


854
00:59:00.950 --> 00:59:03.601
We deserve your help
as citizens of this country.


855
00:59:03.670 --> 00:59:05.035
Citizens under attack.

856
00:59:05.110 --> 00:59:07.954
Now, you listen to me. 
You listen to me.

857
00:59:08.030 --> 00:59:09.919
You're an activist. 
I'm a politician.

858
00:59:09.990 --> 00:59:12.596
You got one big issue.
I got a hundred and one.


859
00:59:12.670 --> 00:59:14.638
Now, you demanding more

860
00:59:14.710 --> 00:59:17.031
and putting me on the spot
with this visit, that's okay.


861
00:59:17.110 --> 00:59:18.874
That's your job. 
That's what you do.

862
00:59:18.950 --> 00:59:21.556
But I am sick and tired

863
00:59:21.630 --> 00:59:26.318
of you demanding and telling me
what I can and what I can't do.


864
00:59:26.390 --> 00:59:28.119
If you want my support
on this voting thing,


865
00:59:28.190 --> 00:59:30.192
I need some quid pro quo from you.

866
00:59:30.670 --> 00:59:32.081
What do you want, Mr. President?

867
00:59:32.150 --> 00:59:35.472
We have a line
on some threats that are

868
00:59:36.990 --> 00:59:38.435
particularly troubling.

869
00:59:38.510 --> 00:59:40.239
Well, what's new?

870
00:59:40.310 --> 00:59:44.918
No, no. This is serious.
Credible threats with detail.


871
00:59:44.990 --> 00:59:47.675
This information,
coming from the FBI, I assume?


872
00:59:48.790 --> 00:59:49.916
High-level?

873
00:59:50.510 --> 00:59:53.912
The same high-level
that's been tracking us like animals?


874
00:59:53.990 --> 00:59:57.676
Bugging our homes
and our hotel rooms.


875
00:59:58.150 --> 01:00:01.757
Digging for things that
simply are not there, Lee?


876
01:00:02.870 --> 01:00:05.350
This all feels very convenient.

877
01:00:06.510 --> 01:00:07.796
Okay.

878
01:00:08.070 --> 01:00:10.755
This is coming
from Lowndes County, Alabama.


879
01:00:10.830 --> 01:00:12.958
Between Selma and Montgomery.

880
01:00:14.750 --> 01:00:17.959
I'm telling you, if he were my guy,

881
01:00:18.030 --> 01:00:20.431
I'd keep him off the frontlines.

882
01:00:21.270 --> 01:00:22.476
Just for a while.

883
01:00:25.510 --> 01:00:26.921
Not gonna happen, Lee.

884
01:00:26.990 --> 01:00:29.197
Meet me halfway on this, Martin.

885
01:00:29.270 --> 01:00:31.318
I can't, Mr. President.

886
01:00:31.430 --> 01:00:33.114
Can't or won't?

887
01:00:33.190 --> 01:00:37.639
I came here hoping
to talk to you about people.


888
01:00:38.350 --> 01:00:40.796
People are dying in the street for this.

889
01:00:40.990 --> 01:00:43.470
It cannot wait, sir.

890
01:00:44.470 --> 01:00:46.472
Mr. President, how did it go?

891
01:00:51.870 --> 01:00:53.520
What can I do to help?

892
01:00:56.230 --> 01:00:58.517
Get me J. Edgar Hoover.

893
01:00:59.790 --> 01:01:01.076
<i>King,</i>

894
01:01:01.950 --> 01:01:04.032
<i>you know you are a complete fraud</i>

895
01:01:04.110 --> 01:01:07.159
<i>and a liability to all nigras.</i>

896
01:01:07.230 --> 01:01:10.359
<i>Like all frauds, your end is approaching.</i>

897
01:01:11.230 --> 01:01:12.834
<i>You are done.</i>

898
01:01:13.590 --> 01:01:18.471
<i>Your degrees and your fancy awards
will not save you.</i>


899
01:01:18.910 --> 01:01:23.837
<i>The American public will
soon know you for what you are,</i>


900
01:01:23.910 --> 01:01:27.278
<i>an evil, abnormal beast.</i>

901
01:01:45.430 --> 01:01:46.955
That wasn't me.

902
01:01:49.990 --> 01:01:51.719
That isn't me, Corrie.

903
01:01:56.190 --> 01:01:57.476
I know.

904
01:01:59.990 --> 01:02:02.641
I know what you sound like.

905
01:02:12.590 --> 01:02:14.638
I've gotten used to a lot.

906
01:02:17.710 --> 01:02:21.556
All the hours
wondering after your safety,


907
01:02:22.990 --> 01:02:25.357
worried about how you are.

908
01:02:30.390 --> 01:02:31.471
This house.

909
01:02:33.670 --> 01:02:34.910
Renting here.

910
01:02:37.150 --> 01:02:38.754
No foundation.

911
01:02:44.070 --> 01:02:46.801
Without the things
the children should have,


912
01:02:46.870 --> 01:02:48.998
all because of how it would look.

913
01:02:54.190 --> 01:02:56.557
I have gotten used to it,

914
01:02:57.470 --> 01:03:00.041
for better or worse.

915
01:03:04.510 --> 01:03:07.798
But what I have never gotten used to

916
01:03:08.110 --> 01:03:10.158
is the death.

917
01:03:12.230 --> 01:03:16.918
The constant closeness of death.

918
01:03:21.390 --> 01:03:24.519
It's become like a thick fog to me.

919
01:03:26.310 --> 01:03:29.473
I can't see life sometimes

920
01:03:29.550 --> 01:03:33.760
because of the fog of death
constantly hanging over.


921
01:03:37.390 --> 01:03:41.031
People actually say that
they will stop the blood


922
01:03:41.110 --> 01:03:44.512
running through the hearts
of our children.


923
01:03:44.590 --> 01:03:47.912
That's what they said on the other end
of that phone line.


924
01:03:51.230 --> 01:03:53.836
How they're going to kill my children.

925
01:03:54.630 --> 01:03:56.997
And what they'll do to you
and how they'll do it.


926
01:03:57.070 --> 01:03:59.516
How many years
have I had to listen to this?


927
01:03:59.590 --> 01:04:00.716
The filth,

928
01:04:00.790 --> 01:04:06.433
deranged and twisted
