01:08:41.030 --> 01:08:42.998
Are you listening to yourself?

986
01:08:43.070 --> 01:08:45.391
First, it's gonna do more for him.
Now, it's why he ain't here?


987
01:08:45.470 --> 01:08:46.915
Do you want him here,
or do you not want him here?


988
01:08:46.990 --> 01:08:49.675
Honestly, I don't give a rat's ass
about that man. That's your hero.


989
01:08:49.750 --> 01:08:52.674
Let's take these bastards
and stick them down into Alabama River


990
01:08:52.750 --> 01:08:53.956
and never see them again.

991
01:08:54.030 --> 01:08:55.475
James, you are so off-base with this.

992
01:08:55.550 --> 01:08:57.314
All this nonsense.
This ain't what SNCC is about.


993
01:08:57.390 --> 01:08:58.516
Don't make me out to be
the bad guy here, John.


994
01:08:58.590 --> 01:09:00.319
I'm not!
You're the one playing me small.


995
01:09:00.390 --> 01:09:02.040
Don't demonize me...

996
01:09:02.430 --> 01:09:04.558
You're mad because they called him in.

997
01:09:05.870 --> 01:09:07.952
We were here first.
And they called him in.


998
01:09:08.070 --> 01:09:10.641
I get it. I understand that.

999
01:09:10.710 --> 01:09:14.032
But if we are really
and truly for the people,


1000
01:09:14.110 --> 01:09:16.431
and the people of Selma chose him,

1001
01:09:17.910 --> 01:09:19.878
well, then the people have spoken.

1002
01:09:21.870 --> 01:09:25.079
And if they want to march,
then I'm marching with them.


1003
01:09:28.230 --> 01:09:29.755
Then, brother,

1004
01:09:30.950 --> 01:09:33.271
you're marching as John Lewis.

1005
01:09:34.070 --> 01:09:35.834
Not as part of SNCC.

1006
01:09:37.750 --> 01:09:39.752
It's been voted on and decided.

1007
01:09:40.710 --> 01:09:44.715
For this march, you're on your own
with De Lawd and his disciples.


1008
01:10:15.790 --> 01:10:17.679
Short man wins. 
Short man wins.

1009
01:10:18.310 --> 01:10:19.800
Short man wins.

1010
01:10:21.430 --> 01:10:22.636
All right.

1011
01:10:24.670 --> 01:10:26.798
All right. Who got it?

1012
01:10:28.510 --> 01:10:30.035
It's on you, Hosea.

1013
01:10:30.150 --> 01:10:32.721
You ready, young blood? You ready?

1014
01:10:32.790 --> 01:10:35.236
- All right. Let's do this.
- All right.


1015
01:10:39.870 --> 01:10:42.601
<i>About 525 Negroes
had left Brown's Chapel</i>


1016
01:10:42.670 --> 01:10:44.354
<i>and walked six blocks to cross
Pettus Bridge</i>


1017
01:10:44.430 --> 01:10:46.194
<i>and the Alabama River.</i>

1018
01:11:02.070 --> 01:11:03.879
There were young and old,

1019
01:11:03.950 --> 01:11:05.759
and they carried
an assortment of packs,


1020
01:11:05.830 --> 01:11:07.912
bed rolls and lunch sacks.

1021
01:12:21.190 --> 01:12:25.240
<i>The troopers were waiting

1022
01:12:26.190 --> 01:12:29.239
<i>Behind the troopers
were dozens of possemen,</i>


1023
01:12:29.750 --> 01:12:34.711
<i>15 of them on horses,
and perhaps 100 white spectators.</i>


1024
01:12:45.110 --> 01:12:46.839
Can you swim?

1025
01:12:47.830 --> 01:12:51.391
Not many swimming pools for black folk
where I come from.


1026
01:12:52.430 --> 01:12:54.080
Yeah.

1027
01:13:21.710 --> 01:13:23.838
<i>Andy, it's Bayard. 
Everybody there?</i>

1028
01:13:24.110 --> 01:13:25.111
Yes.

1029
01:13:25.190 --> 01:13:26.396
<i>Turn on CBS right now, Andy.</i>

1030
01:13:26.470 --> 01:13:27.710
Right now. You have a TV there?

1031
01:13:27.990 --> 01:13:29.879
- Yes. Now?
- Right now!


1032
01:13:30.190 --> 01:13:31.954
Turn on the television set.

1033
01:13:32.870 --> 01:13:37.034
<i>We interrupt this program to bring you
a special bulletin from CBS News.</i>


1034
01:13:52.910 --> 01:13:55.231
Give 'em two minutes. 
Stand right there.

1035
01:13:55.310 --> 01:13:56.675
We're ready.

1036
01:14:09.990 --> 01:14:11.992
<i>This is an unlawful assembly.</i>

1037
01:14:12.070 --> 01:14:14.391
<i>You have two minutes to disperse.</i>

1038
01:14:14.470 --> 01:14:17.201
<i>Go home or go to your church.</i>

1039
01:14:17.390 --> 01:14:20.473
<i>This march will not continue.</i>

1040
01:14:21.030 --> 01:14:22.839
Two minutes.

1041
01:14:26.150 --> 01:14:28.835
May I have a word with the Major?

1042
01:14:31.230 --> 01:14:33.073
<i>There's no word to be had.</i>

1043
01:14:35.470 --> 01:14:37.393
Major Cloud, may we speak with you?

1044
01:14:50.510 --> 01:14:52.114
<i>Troopers, advance!</i>

1045
01:15:07.790 --> 01:15:10.441
Seventy million people
are watching this.


1046
01:15:10.510 --> 01:15:12.433
<i>The first 10 or 20 Negroes</i>

1047
01:15:12.510 --> 01:15:15.275
<i>were swept to the ground screaming,
arms and legs flying,</i>


1048
01:15:15.350 --> 01:15:18.513
<i>packs and bags went skittering
across the grassy divider.</i>


1049
01:15:33.390 --> 01:15:35.836
<i>Those still on their feet retreated.</i>

1050
01:15:35.910 --> 01:15:37.958
<i>A cheer went up
from the white spectators</i>


1051
01:15:38.030 --> 01:15:39.680
<i>lining the south side of the highway.</i>

1052
01:15:46.150 --> 01:15:49.040
Come on. You gotta come on.

1053
01:15:49.110 --> 01:15:50.236
Please, don't...

1054
01:15:51.830 --> 01:15:54.993
<i>The troopers continued pushing,
using both the force of their bodies</i>


1055
01:15:55.070 --> 01:15:56.515
<i>and the prodding of their nightsticks.</i>

1056
01:16:11.110 --> 01:16:14.831
<i>Suddenly, there was a sharp sound,
like a gunshot,</i>


1057
01:16:14.910 --> 01:16:19.040
<i>and a gray cloud spewed over
the troopers and the Negroes.</i>


1058
01:16:19.110 --> 01:16:21.590
<i>But before the cloud hid it all,</i>

1059
01:16:21.710 --> 01:16:25.874
there were several seconds
of unobstructed view.


1060
01:16:46.230 --> 01:16:50.315
<i>Fifteen or 20 nightsticks
could be seen through the gas,</i>


1061
01:16:50.390 --> 01:16:53.041
<i>flailing at the heads of the marchers.</i>

1062
01:16:54.590 --> 01:16:57.799
<i>The Negroes cried out
as they crowded together for protection,</i>


1063
01:16:57.870 --> 01:17:00.032
<i>and the whites on the sidelines
whooped and cheered.</i>


1064
01:17:12.830 --> 01:17:15.515
<i>From the hospital
came reports of victims</i>


1065
01:17:15.590 --> 01:17:19.834
<i>suffering fractures of ribs,
heads, arms and legs.</i>


1066
01:17:19.910 --> 01:17:21.912
<i>And Negro leader John Lewis,</i>

1067
01:17:21.990 --> 01:17:24.311
<i>despite injury from
a possible skull fracture,</i>


1068
01:17:24.390 --> 01:17:26.199
<i>led the marchers back to the chapel</i>

1069
01:17:26.270 --> 01:17:28.352
<i>after the encounter with officers.</i>

1070
01:17:29.270 --> 01:17:30.715
Help!

1071
01:17:31.230 --> 01:17:32.231
Help!

1072
01:17:36.990 --> 01:17:40.881
<i>He said,
"I don't see how President Johnson</i>


1073
01:17:40.950 --> 01:17:42.361
<i>"can send troops to Vietnam</i>

1074
01:17:42.630 --> 01:17:46.396
"and can't send troops
to Selma, Alabama."


1075
01:17:46.470 --> 01:17:50.600
To which the Negroes present
roared their approval.


1076
01:18:32.750 --> 01:18:35.196
Gerry! Gerry, come with us!
Come with us!


1077
01:18:35.270 --> 01:18:36.556
We need your gun, man!

1078
01:18:36.630 --> 01:18:37.995
I can't walk!

1079
01:18:38.070 --> 01:18:40.676
Come with us. We know you got
them guns in the shed, Gerry.


1080
01:18:40.750 --> 01:18:43.117
Hey, hey, hey, what you need guns for?

1081
01:18:43.190 --> 01:18:44.874
The Bible says,
"An eye for an eye," Reverend.


1082
01:18:44.950 --> 01:18:46.520
- Yeah?
- I'm sick of this shit!


1083
01:18:46.590 --> 01:18:48.672
How many guns
you think they got down there?


1084
01:18:48.750 --> 01:18:50.639
That's an entire army down there.

1085
01:18:50.710 --> 01:18:53.031
What you got? A
couple of .32s? A .38?

1086
01:18:53.110 --> 01:18:54.441
Maybe a couple of old scatterguns?
What?


1087
01:18:54.510 --> 01:18:57.036
I got enough to kill a couple
of them crackers, that's what I got!


1088
01:18:57.110 --> 01:19:00.398
And how many of us you think
they gonna kill in retaliation?


1089
01:19:00.470 --> 01:19:03.599
With their 12-gauge pump-actions,
their Colt automatics,


1090
01:19:03.670 --> 01:19:06.150
their Remingtons,
their helicopters, their tanks!


1091
01:19:06.870 --> 01:19:10.272
We won't win that way,
and I ain't talking about the Bible.


1092
01:19:10.470 --> 01:19:14.794
I ain't talking what's right by God.
I am talking facts. Cold, hard facts!


1093
01:19:14.870 --> 01:19:19.239
Now, you take two of them,
and they take 10 of us.


1094
01:19:19.310 --> 01:19:22.917
No. We have to win another way.

1095
01:19:24.310 --> 01:19:26.472
<i>...to our regularly scheduled program.</i>

1096
01:19:34.150 --> 01:19:36.198
We're going back to the bridge.

1097
01:19:39.670 --> 01:19:43.197
We're going to finish this,
we promise you that, Ms. Amelia.


1098
01:19:46.430 --> 01:19:48.273
We go again.

1099
01:19:53.390 --> 01:19:56.121
Dr. King! Can we get a statement, sir?

1100
01:19:56.190 --> 01:19:59.000
Dr. King! Morning, Doctor.
Can we get a statement, please?


1101
01:19:59.070 --> 01:20:00.481
- Morning.
- Morning.


1102
01:20:01.950 --> 01:20:07.320
While rageful violence continues
towards the unarmed people of Selma,


1103
01:20:07.670 --> 01:20:13.439
while they are assaulted with tear gas
and batons like an enemy in a war,


1104
01:20:13.510 --> 01:20:17.071
no citizen of this country
can call themselves blameless,


1105
01:20:17.150 --> 01:20:20.836
for we all bear a responsibility
for our fellow man.


1106
01:20:21.470 --> 01:20:24.474
I am appealing to
men and women of God


1107
01:20:24.550 --> 01:20:26.552
and goodwill everywhere,

1108
01:20:26.630 --> 01:20:28.951
white, black and otherwise.

1109
01:20:29.030 --> 01:20:34.799
If you believe all are created equal,
come to Selma.


1110
01:20:34.870 --> 01:20:39.319
Join us. Join our march
against injustice and inhumanity.


1111
01:20:40.230 --> 01:20:41.880
We need you to stand with us.

1112
01:20:44.590 --> 01:20:47.514
<i>Judge Johnson, Dr. 
King's call-to-action</i>

1113
01:20:47.590 --> 01:20:49.319
<i>was nationally televised.</i>

1114
01:20:50.710 --> 01:20:52.838
<i>We've seen hundreds of people
travel across the country</i>


1115
01:20:52.910 --> 01:20:54.674
<i>to attend tomorrow's march,</i>

1116
01:20:54.750 --> 01:20:58.835
<i>mostly white,
mostly clergy of some kind.</i>


1117
01:21:00.350 --> 01:21:03.559
The SCLC is seeking
a federal court order


1118
01:21:03.630 --> 01:21:07.112
enjoining the state authorities
from interfering with the next march.


1119
01:21:08.190 --> 01:21:10.557
You're asking me to overturn
the Governor's mandate


1120
01:21:10.630 --> 01:21:12.678
and to do so without a hearing,

1121
01:21:12.750 --> 01:21:16.072
but it's not going to happen at all
without a proper proceeding.


1122
01:21:16.150 --> 01:21:19.120
Dr. King is in position to
lead tomorrow's march, Judge.


1123
01:21:19.190 --> 01:21:23.195
Understood, but you will have
your day in court on Thursday, Mr. Gray.


1124
01:21:23.270 --> 01:21:26.080
Meanwhile, there will be
no march tomorrow.


1125
01:21:26.150 --> 01:21:28.676
I will not oppose Wallace
against protocol.


1126
01:21:29.990 --> 01:21:32.914
"Thousands head south
in moral crusade."


1127
01:21:36.630 --> 01:21:40.999
The SCLC already filed an appeal
against Wallace's orders this morning.


1128
01:21:43.590 --> 01:21:45.558
You want my advice, Mr. President?

1129
01:21:45.950 --> 01:21:47.475
You have to ask?

1130
01:21:47.710 --> 01:21:50.554
Give King the march to Montgomery.

1131
01:21:52.430 --> 01:21:55.593
Do that, and then Selma's over.

1132
01:21:57.030 --> 01:21:58.191
Then you're back in control.

1133
01:21:58.350 --> 01:22:00.352
In control of what?

1134
01:22:00.430 --> 01:22:02.319
Another civil war?

1135
01:22:02.390 --> 01:22:05.837
This ain't about the goddamn march.
You think he cares about the march?


1136
01:22:05.910 --> 01:22:08.516
He wants the law changed, now.

1137
01:22:08.870 --> 01:22:10.599
I've got Congress
calling me by the dozens.


1138
01:22:10.670 --> 01:22:13.150
I've got picketing that gets
bigger and bigger every day.


1139
01:22:13.270 --> 01:22:15.841
He tugs on their goddamn
white liberal conscience.


1140
01:22:16.310 --> 01:22:17.277
Every march pulls 'em.

1141
01:22:17.350 --> 01:22:20.320
Especially when people
are getting beat up in the streets.


1142
01:22:23.790 --> 01:22:26.236
These pictures are
going around the world, Lee.


1143
01:22:26.630 --> 01:22:30.237
I understand, Mr. President.
All the more reason to act now.


1144
01:22:30.310 --> 01:22:31.357
I'm gonna act now.

1145
01:22:32.310 --> 01:22:34.916
You tell Wallace
and those backwater hicks


1146
01:22:34.990 --> 01:22:37.072
I don't want to see any more
of this horseshit.


1147
01:22:37.150 --> 01:22:40.279
And you tell King he best not march,
you hear me?


1148
01:22:40.350 --> 01:22:43.797
Either King stops and Wallace stops,

1149
01:22:43.870 --> 01:22:45.838
or I'll stop 'em both.

1150
01:22:45.990 --> 01:22:49.437
I'm here on the President's order
to try and make this work.


1151
01:22:50.710 --> 01:22:52.235
Please work with me.

1152
01:22:53.510 --> 01:22:55.353
So we give up the march and you...

1153
01:22:56.390 --> 01:22:57.755
You give what?

1154
01:22:58.710 --> 01:23:00.235
We asked for federal protection.

1155
01:23:00.310 --> 01:23:01.800
And with no disrespect,

1156
01:23:01.870 --> 01:23:03.360
but when the Assistant Attorney General

1157
01:23:03.430 --> 01:23:05.512
is the highest-ranking
federal official in Selma,


1158
01:23:05.590 --> 01:23:07.797
we have our answer.

1159
01:23:07.910 --> 01:23:09.150
And it's not the one we want.

1160
01:23:09.230 --> 01:23:13.952
Might I suggest that
you speak with Governor Wallace


1161
01:23:14.030 --> 01:23:16.636
and Sheriff Clark
and urge them against violence


1162
01:23:16.750 --> 01:23:20.391
instead of trying to persuade us
not to have a peaceful protest?


1163
01:23:26.270 --> 01:23:28.193
Maybe we can make a deal.

1164
01:23:29.470 --> 01:23:31.120
What if I

1165
01:23:31.790 --> 01:23:33.997
could assure you that the administration

1166
01:23:34.070 --> 01:23:36.755
would endorse a later march

1167
01:23:37.230 --> 01:23:38.561
if tomorrow is called off?

1168
01:23:40.270 --> 01:23:44.559
You know what?
He's closer than you may think


1169
01:23:44.630 --> 01:23:47.281
to coming around on this issue.

1170
01:23:48.190 --> 01:23:50.716
I believe this compromise
might be agreeable.


1171
01:23:50.790 --> 01:23:52.030
Mr. Doar?

1172
01:23:53.070 --> 01:23:57.598
Thousands have gathered here
to demonstrate their dignity.


1173
01:23:59.270 --> 01:24:01.159
I don't want to
challenge Judge Johnson.


1174
01:24:01.230 --> 01:24:04.439
I don't want to go against the President.
I don't want any of this.


1175
01:24:05.270 --> 01:24:08.035
The President could stop this
with a stroke of his pen.


1176
01:24:08.110 --> 01:24:10.238
He chooses not to.

1177
01:24:10.310 --> 01:24:12.790
The decision is with your side, sir,

1178
01:24:13.830 --> 01:24:14.991
not ours.

1179
01:24:24.350 --> 01:24:26.114
Good to see you, Father.
Good to see you.


1180
01:24:26.190 --> 01:24:27.555
Thank you for coming.
Thank you for coming out.


1181
01:24:27.630 --> 01:24:29.553
Hello, sister.
Good to see you this afternoon.


1182
01:24:31.510 --> 01:24:33.000
You came.

1183
01:24:33.190 --> 01:24:36.876
You called and we came, my friend.
You are not alone, my friend.


1184
01:24:36.950 --> 01:24:38.111
Welcome, welcome.

1185
01:24:38.190 --> 01:24:39.635
- Hi, what's your name?
- Susan.


1186
01:24:39.750 --> 01:24:41.434
Hi, I'm Viola. 
Welcome to Selma.

1187
01:24:42.070 --> 01:24:44.357
- Yes, ma'am, I'm good. How are you?
- Fine, thank you.


1188
01:24:44.430 --> 01:24:46.034
What is your name
and where are you from, sir?


1189
01:24:46.110 --> 01:24:48.920
My name is James Reeb.
I've come from Boston.


1190
01:24:48.990 --> 01:24:52.312
Tell me, why have you traveled here,
Mr. Reeb?


1191
01:24:52.950 --> 01:24:56.750
I heard about the attack
of innocent people


1192
01:24:56.830 --> 01:24:58.195
who just want their rights,

1193
01:24:58.510 --> 01:25:03.471
and I couldn't just stand by
when Dr. King put out that call to clergy.


1194
01:25:03.550 --> 01:25:04.756
I couldn't.

1195
01:25:04.950 --> 01:25:07.681
<i>The President doesn't
want us to march today.</i>


1196
01:25:08.350 --> 01:25:10.637
<i>The courts don't want us to march.</i>

1197
01:25:10.790 --> 01:25:11.791
<i>But we must march.</i>

1198
01:25:11.870 --> 01:25:12.917
Yeah!

1199
01:25:12.990 --> 01:25:14.719
<i>- We must stand up.</i>
- Yeah!


1200
01:25:14.790 --> 01:25:18.636
<i>We must make a massive
demonstration of our moral certainty.</i>


1201
01:25:22.350 --> 01:25:26.071
<i>I'm so glad we're here together today.</i>

1202
01:25:26.350 --> 01:25:28.717
<i>I thank you for standing up.</i>

1203
01:25:28.910 --> 01:25:32.073
<i>For we shall be victorious in our quest.</i>

1204
01:25:32.150 --> 01:25:35.120
<i>We shall cross the finish line
hand in hand.</i>


1205
01:25:36.550 --> 01:25:40.680
<i>For we shall overcome. 
All right.</i>

1206
01:27:17.830 --> 01:27:20.515
<i>Troopers, withdraw!</i>

1207
01:29:46.630 --> 01:29:48.632
My point is,
after what happened the last time,


1208
01:29:48.710 --> 01:29:50.838
if it don't feel right, we don't do it.
That's my point.


1209
01:29:50.910 --> 01:29:52.753
We've been going round
and round on this for hours,


1210
01:29:52.830 --> 01:29:54.355
and nothing's gonna
change the fact that


1211
01:29:54.430 --> 01:29:56.319
it was Doc's decision
and we have to support him.


1212
01:29:56.390 --> 01:29:57.960
This is a movement
of many, not of one.

1213
01:29:58.070 --> 01:29:59.595
So any choice we make
has to be right for many.


1214
01:29:59.670 --> 01:30:00.910
Come on, Diane. Now, you know

1215
01:30:01.030 --> 01:30:02.191
that's not what I
meant by that, all right?

1216
01:30:02.270 --> 01:30:04.557
People are angry, Dr. King.

1217
01:30:05.070 --> 01:30:09.917
Angry. They went back to that bridge
because they were hot about Sunday.


1218
01:30:09.990 --> 01:30:11.913
That was our moment out there today.

1219
01:30:11.990 --> 01:30:13.355
And you threw it away.

1220
01:30:13.910 --> 01:30:16.356
They could've sealed off
the road behind us.


1221
01:30:16.430 --> 01:30:20.355
No food, water,
no kind of support allowed through.


1222
01:30:21.150 --> 01:30:22.640
We wouldn't have made 10 miles.

1223
01:30:22.710 --> 01:30:24.075
You saying this was a trap?

1224
01:30:27.510 --> 01:30:28.841
I don't know what it was.

1225
01:30:29.550 --> 01:30:31.757
That was no trap!

1226
01:30:31.830 --> 01:30:33.719
You know why they opened up
the road to us?


1227
01:30:34.150 --> 01:30:37.074
Because all them nice,
respectable white folks was with us,


1228
01:30:37.190 --> 01:30:38.954
and we should've capitalized on that.

1229
01:30:39.030 --> 01:30:41.317
Because they're not gonna be
around here for long. They never are!


1230
01:30:41.390 --> 01:30:43.631
It was Martin's call. It's done.

1231
01:30:43.710 --> 01:30:45.519
He made the wrong goddamn call!

1232
01:30:45.590 --> 01:30:46.955
Hey, watch your mouth, young man!

1233
01:30:47.030 --> 01:30:49.636
Two days ago,
you didn't wanna march at all.


1234
01:30:49.710 --> 01:30:52.111
And now you're mad because
it didn't go the way you planned?


1235
01:30:52.190 --> 01:30:53.874
Calm down, brother.

1236
01:30:57.910 --> 01:31:01.437
Now, what happened out there today?
You gotta tell us something. Please.


1237
01:31:09.110 --> 01:31:11.841
I'd rather people be upset and hate me

1238
01:31:11.910 --> 01:31:14.914
than be bleeding or dead.

1239
01:32:09.910 --> 01:32:12.561
<i>My dearest Corrie,</i>

1240
01:32:14.550 --> 01:32:16.632
<i>at a time when I need you,</i>

1241
01:32:17.630 --> 01:32:19.598
<i>I cannot call you.</i>

1242
01:32:21.110 --> 01:32:25.832
<i>And I have done
this to myself, to us.</i>

1243
01:32:29.470 --> 01:32:31.518
<i>At this late hour,</i>

1244
01:32:32.710 --> 01:32:34.997
<i>my thoughts are of you</i>

1245
01:32:35.110 --> 01:32:38.876
<i>and all you have sacrificed
for this struggle.</i>


1246
01:32:40.390 --> 01:32:43.360
<i>So many have sacrificed.</i>

1247
01:32:44.430 --> 01:32:46.876
<i>So many have been lost.</i>

1248
01:32:48.150 --> 01:32:51.757
<i>I wonder how many must we lose.</i>

1249
01:32:55.670 --> 01:33:00.801
<i>I pray for discernment and guidance
as we journey on.</i>


1250
01:33:02.390 --> 01:33:06.952
<i>I pray, too, that I can justify
the faith you once had in me.</i>


1251
01:33:09.630 --> 01:33:16.275
<i>I, too, often feel that
heavy fog you spoke of, Corrie.</i>


1252
01:33:18.790 --> 01:33:23.796
<i>Only you and our family clears the haze.</i>

1253
01:33:26.190 --> 01:33:29.080
<i>Love, Martin.</i>

1254
01:33:31.950 --> 01:33:33.156
<i>He betrayed trust.</i>

1255
01:33:33.630 --> 01:33:36.839
He called, we came,
and he didn't fulfill his own call.


1256
01:33:36.910 --> 01:33:39.038
Yeah, but sometimes
it's not that clear-cut.


1257
01:33:39.110 --> 01:33:41.397
Sometimes it's instinctual.

1258
01:33:42.350 --> 01:33:44.034
Like when you're preaching,

1259
01:33:44.710 --> 01:33:46.439
and you're just flying.

1260
01:33:47.710 --> 01:33:50.873
You know, you're not on the notes.
You're not on memory.


1261
01:33:50.950 --> 01:33:55.433
You're tapped into what's higher,
what's true.


1262
01:33:56.310 --> 01:33:57.641
God is guiding you.

1263
01:33:59.310 --> 01:34:02.519
I've known that feeling.
It's rare, but I've known it.


1264
01:34:05.990 --> 01:34:09.790
I think that's what happened to Dr. King
up there on the bridge today.


1265
01:34:09.870 --> 01:34:12.350
He kneeled down,
prayed to God and got an answer.


1266
01:34:12.430 --> 01:34:15.320
And he was brave enough
to follow that answer,


1267
01:34:15.390 --> 01:34:18.280
and I, for one,
don't fault him for it.

1268
01:34:18.350 --> 01:34:20.637
Except he owes me a bus ticket home.

1269
01:34:21.310 --> 01:34:22.675
You know what
I hate more than niggers?


1270
01:34:22.790 --> 01:34:24.121
What's that?

1271
01:34:24.750 --> 01:34:25.876
White niggers.

1272
01:34:26.790 --> 01:34:28.315
Look, we don't want trouble, okay?

1273
01:34:28.390 --> 01:34:30.154
No, you came here stirrin' trouble.

1274
01:34:47.550 --> 01:34:48.597
Doc,

1275
01:34:50.510 --> 01:34:51.875
someone's been hurt.

1276
01:34:56.630 --> 01:34:59.679
A priest, from Boston.

1277
01:35:01.230 --> 01:35:02.391
<i>White.</i>

1278
01:35:03.670 --> 01:35:06.321
Now you know what
being a nigger around here


1279
01:35:06.390 --> 01:35:08.154
feels like, boy.

1280
01:35:08.670 --> 01:35:10.957
Hurt? How?

1281
01:35:17.830 --> 01:35:18.956
Dead.

1282
01:35:34.790 --> 01:35:36.315
I need a phone!

1283
01:35:37.670 --> 01:35:41.561
Chicago, Detroit, Boston, I don't care.

1284
01:35:41.630 --> 01:35:44.236
Hell, you got 2,000 people
marching up in Harlem.


1285
01:35:44.310 --> 01:35:45.391
Well, good for you.

1286
01:35:45.470 --> 01:35:48.041
<i>But when you have people
come inside the White House?</i>


1287
01:35:48.110 --> 01:35:50.795
Inside the White House! On a tour?

1288
01:35:51.150 --> 01:35:52.436
<i>They just sat down, Martin.</i>

1289
01:35:52.510 --> 01:35:55.195
They sat down in the main corridor,
started singin' and shoutin'.


1290
01:35:55.350 --> 01:35:56.511
Well, I won't have it!

1291
01:35:56.590 --> 01:35:58.001
I cannot stop people from expressing...

1292
01:35:58.070 --> 01:35:59.754
You can! You can stop them.

1293
01:36:00.030 --> 01:36:03.716
No, you can stop it.
You, sir, can do more.


1294
01:36:03.790 --> 01:36:06.953
Now I'm glad to hear that you
called Reverend Reeb's widow, sir.


1295
01:36:07.030 --> 01:36:08.998
That is very fine, and it is right.

1296
01:36:09.070 --> 01:36:11.038
<i>I only wish that
Jimmie Lee Jackson's family</i>


1297
01:36:11.150 --> 01:36:12.640
would have received
the same consideration


1298
01:36:12.710 --> 01:36:13.757
from their President.

1299
01:36:13.830 --> 01:36:15.832
Don't you lay your guilt at my door.

1300
01:36:15.910 --> 01:36:17.321
You're the one choosing to send

1301
01:36:17.390 --> 01:36:20.041
people out to slaughter
when we told you there was trouble.


1302
01:36:20.110 --> 01:36:21.271
<i>We won't sit idle</i>

1303
01:36:21.350 --> 01:36:24.115
while you wait another year or two
to send this bill up at your leisure.


1304
01:36:24.190 --> 01:36:26.272
<i>That should be clear by now.</i>

1305
01:36:26.350 --> 01:36:30.196
<i>We will continue to demonstrate
until you take action, sir.</i>


1306
01:36:30.270 --> 01:36:32.432
<i>And if our President
won't protect our rights,</i>


1307
01:36:32.510 --> 01:36:33.921
<i>we will take this fight to court.</i>

1308
01:36:34.990 --> 01:36:37.277
You know, I'm... 
I'm trying here.

1309
01:36:37.350 --> 01:36:39.000
We're getting close
to figuring something out


1310
01:36:39.070 --> 01:36:41.994
on this voting thing,
but I will not have this!


1311
01:36:43.390 --> 01:36:47.076
<i>This bill has been almost impossible
to craft, you hear me?</i>


1312
01:36:47.150 --> 01:36:50.552
<i>You think you're jugglin', Martin?
I'm jugglin', too.</i>


1313
01:36:52.310 --> 01:36:54.438
I am a preacher from Atlanta.

1314
01:36:54.830 --> 01:36:56.832
You are the man
who won the presidency


1315
01:36:56.910 --> 01:36:58.639
of the world's most powerful nation

1316
01:36:58.710 --> 01:37:02.032
<i>by the greatest landslide
in history four months ago.</i>


1317
01:37:02.390 --> 01:37:03.630
<i>And you are the man</i>

1318
01:37:03.710 --> 01:37:07.920
dismantling your own legacy
with each passing day.


1319
01:37:09.310 --> 01:37:11.392
<i>No one will remember
the Civil Rights Act.</i>


1320
01:37:11.910 --> 01:37:14.516
But they will remember
the standoff in Selma


1321
01:37:14.630 --> 01:37:17.315
when you never even
set foot in this state.


1322
01:37:17.390 --> 01:37:20.951
<i>They will remember you saying,
"Wait," and "I can't,"</i>


1323
01:37:21.030 --> 01:37:24.432
unless you act, sir.

1324
01:37:36.270 --> 01:37:38.159
- Evenin'.
- Evenin'.


1325
01:37:54.310 --> 01:37:56.631
I wanted to speak privately.

1326
01:37:57.590 --> 01:38:00.355
I know there's been trouble
with the group,


1327
01:38:00.430 --> 01:38:04.799
and I apologize that our efforts
have caused a rift between y'all.


1328
01:38:06.470 --> 01:38:10.111
That's a painful thing, I know,
and I'm truly sorry it's happened.


1329
01:38:11.590 --> 01:38:14.594
Yeah, painful.

1330
01:38:20.430 --> 01:38:23.161
LBJ is not moving, John.

1331
01:38:24.390 --> 01:38:26.916
I thought he would,
but our efforts are not working,


1332
01:38:26.990 --> 01:38:29.357
and I can't risk another march
with people getting killed


1333
01:38:29.430 --> 01:38:31.194
when it's not working. 
I won't do it.

1334
01:38:32.310 --> 01:38:35.393
We need voting, not marching.
You know that.


1335
01:38:36.190 --> 01:38:40.639
We have to move beyond these protests
to some real political power.


1336
01:38:40.710 --> 01:38:43.031
This can't go on forever like this.

1337
01:38:44.710 --> 01:38:46.678
I can't go on like this.

1338
01:39:02.510 --> 01:39:04.080
When I was...

1339
01:39:06.030 --> 01:39:09.955
When I was working with SNCC
on the Freedom Rides,


1340
01:39:12.630 --> 01:39:16.112
the Montgomery bus
reached the city limits.


1341
01:39:17.790 --> 01:39:20.236
We got off. And out of nowhere,

1342
01:39:21.630 --> 01:39:25.601
from all directions, they came.

1343
01:39:28.310 --> 01:39:31.598
There was men, women.

1344
01:39:33.710 --> 01:39:35.155
Kids, too.

1345
01:39:38.270 --> 01:39:42.639
They had just about every makeshift
weapon you could think of.


1346
01:39:42.710 --> 01:39:45.441
I mean, bats, bricks,

1347
01:39:46.710 --> 01:39:50.271
tire irons, pipes.

1348
01:39:54.070 --> 01:39:55.799
I remember...

1349
01:39:57.230 --> 01:40:01.394
I remember this little girl
just clawing her nails


1350
01:40:01.470 --> 01:40:05.395
into the side of my friend Jessie's face

1351
01:40:05.510 --> 01:40:09.595
while her daddy...
Her daddy beat him with an ax handle.


1352
01:40:12.710 --> 01:40:14.519
Jessie was unconscious,

1353
01:40:14.590 --> 01:40:18.072
and they just kept beating on him
and beating on him.


1354
01:40:22.110 --> 01:40:25.432
I must've passed out
on the asphalt somewhere.


1355
01:40:29.030 --> 01:40:34.833
Next day, I found myself patched up
and sitting in a church.


1356
01:40:35.630 --> 01:40:39.191
I could barely hold my head up,
but I needed to be there.


1357
01:40:41.110 --> 01:40:43.192
You were gonna be speaking.

1358
01:40:44.070 --> 01:40:46.232
And I needed to hear you.

1359
01:40:48.910 --> 01:40:51.834
And I was feeling down,
but you got up there.


1360
01:40:54.430 --> 01:40:56.000
You remember that day at all?

1361
01:40:57.710 --> 01:41:00.520
I don't think we remember it
the same way.


1362
01:41:02.030 --> 01:41:03.634
What'd I say, John?

1363
01:41:04.990 --> 01:41:07.311
I'm about to tell you right now.

1364
01:41:08.630 --> 01:41:10.519
And I hope you hear me.

1365
01:41:12.830 --> 01:41:15.276
You said that we would triumph.

1366
01:41:16.070 --> 01:41:19.677
That we would triumph
because there could be no other way.


1367
01:41:23.750 --> 01:41:25.673
And you know what else you said?

1368
01:41:30.710 --> 01:41:31.757
You said,

1369
01:41:32.750 --> 01:41:34.195
"Fear not.

1370
01:41:35.590 --> 01:41:38.594
"We've come too far to turn back now."

1371
01:41:50.590 --> 01:41:54.117
I feel good about where we are.
We have a strong case.


1372
01:41:54.190 --> 01:41:55.521
- We can do this.
- Right.


1373
01:41:56.870 --> 01:41:59.919
Now, Ms. Cooper
and Ms. Boynton are here,


1374
01:41:59.990 --> 01:42:02.277
and they need to be ready.

1375
01:42:03.630 --> 01:42:06.634
A lot depends
on what they have to say. Okay?


1376
01:42:06.710 --> 01:42:08.200
I hear what you're saying, but...

1377
01:42:30.190 --> 01:42:31.555
You're here.

1378
01:42:34.030 --> 01:42:35.839
Yes, I'm here.

1379
01:42:41.510 --> 01:42:42.750
I'm glad.

1380
01:42:56.750 --> 01:42:58.718
Just in time.

1381
01:42:59.070 --> 01:43:01.437
In the matter of the <i>Southern
Christian Leadership Conference</i>


1382
01:43:01.510 --> 01:43:02.921
<i>v. the state of Alabama,</i>

1383
01:43:02.990 --> 01:43:06.551
I will now hear testimony
from the plaintiffs. Mr. Gray.


1384
01:43:07.710 --> 01:43:10.031
Your Honor, you will hear testimony
from the victims


1385
01:43:10.150 --> 01:43:13.393
who were beaten and bludgeoned
in their quest for freedom.


1386
01:43:13.470 --> 01:43:16.440
For their right to vote
and to self-determine.


1387
01:43:17.150 --> 01:43:18.276
The fact of the matter, Your Honor,

1388
01:43:18.350 --> 01:43:21.320
is that the incidents that occurred
cannot be disputed.


1389
01:43:21.750 --> 01:43:24.151
These particular circumstances

1390
01:43:24.670 --> 01:43:30.120
will paint a thorough picture
of the horrific events endured in Selma.


1391
01:43:30.790 --> 01:43:32.997
Very well, you may proceed.

1392
01:43:33.070 --> 01:43:37.200
Mr. King, you went out on that bridge
in direct violation of that judge's orders.


1393
01:43:37.910 --> 01:43:41.357
You deliberately disobeyed this judge
and the Governor, did you not?


1394
01:43:42.630 --> 01:43:45.713
Thousands of people came to Selma,

1395
01:43:45.790 --> 01:43:48.794
aroused by Sunday's brutal acts

1396
01:43:49.190 --> 01:43:52.876
exacted by officials of the city of Selma

1397
01:43:52.950 --> 01:43:54.793
and the state of Alabama.

1398
01:43:54.870 --> 01:43:57.874
I felt if I
had not led the march,

1399
01:43:57.990 --> 01:44:02.234
pent-up emotions and inner tensions
would have led to an uncontrollable


1400
01:44:02.310 --> 01:44:04.392
retaliatory situation,

1401
01:44:05.790 --> 01:44:08.236
a violent situation on both sides.

1402
01:44:08.310 --> 01:44:10.119
I don't need any of your preaching
and prancing in here,


1403
01:44:10.190 --> 01:44:11.476
you hear? I want an answer.

1404
01:44:11.550 --> 01:44:14.076
- Objection.
- Watch it, counselor.


1405
01:44:14.590 --> 01:44:15.830
I'm trying very hard, Judge.

1406
01:44:16.190 --> 01:44:17.555
Try harder, counselor.

1407
01:44:23.230 --> 01:44:26.439
<i>It seems basic to
our constitutional principles</i>


1408
01:44:26.510 --> 01:44:29.719
<i>that the extent of the right to assemble,</i>

1409
01:44:30.510 --> 01:44:32.274
<i>and demonstrate and march</i>

1410
01:44:32.350 --> 01:44:34.000
<i>along the highway in a peaceful manner</i>

1411
01:44:34.110 --> 01:44:35.760
<i>ought to be commensurate</i>

1412
01:44:35.830 --> 01:44:38.037
<i>with the enormity of the wrongs</i>

1413
01:44:38.110 --> 01:44:40.841
<i>that are being protested
and petitioned against.</i>


1414
01:44:41.670 --> 01:44:46.198
<i>In this case, the wrongs are enormous.</i>

1415
01:44:48.670 --> 01:44:49.796
<i>Therefore,</i>

1416
01:44:50.790 --> 01:44:54.033
the extent of the right to demonstrate

1417
01:44:54.110 --> 01:44:57.592
in an estimated five-day march
from Selma to Montgomery


1418
01:44:58.270 --> 01:44:59.954
has been approved accordingly.

1419
01:45:00.230 --> 01:45:02.232
- Yes!
- Thank God!


1420
01:45:04.030 --> 01:45:06.795
There's no further business
with this court.


1421
01:45:06.870 --> 01:45:10.591
These proceedings are concluded,
with our thanks to the litigants.


1422
01:45:11.910 --> 01:45:13.719
Good day, gentlemen.

1423
01:45:29.150 --> 01:45:30.197
Yeah, that's right.

1424
01:45:30.270 --> 01:45:33.080
Well, now, we don't like
to have no mistakes, if you...


1425
01:45:33.150 --> 01:45:34.311
If you're sure about it.

1426
01:45:35.390 --> 01:45:39.031
Bayard says that Harry says
he can get Nina Simone,


1427
01:45:39.110 --> 01:45:43.240
Dick Gregory, Joan Baez,
Peter, Paul and Mary in.


1428
01:45:44.190 --> 01:45:45.794
Come on now.
We don't got money for that.


1429
01:45:45.870 --> 01:45:48.350
Well, Harry is chartering
a plane himself.


1430
01:45:48.470 --> 01:45:51.440
<i>Day
-O, day
-O</i>

1431
01:45:52.350 --> 01:45:56.241
<i>Daylight come
and me wan' go home</i>


1432
01:45:56.310 --> 01:46:01.680
President's angling for your blocking
of the march to be overturned.


1433
01:46:02.350 --> 01:46:04.956
Unfortunately, all my maneuvers
have been put on hold


1434
01:46:05.030 --> 01:46:07.874
while the matter's being adjudicated.

1435
01:46:16.390 --> 01:46:17.630
<i>Governor, you wanted to talk.</i>

1436
01:46:18.630 --> 01:46:20.837
Well, Mr. President...

1437
01:46:21.430 --> 01:46:27.278
Malcontents are disrupting Alabama,
and it's your responsibility to stop them.


1438
01:46:28.030 --> 01:46:30.715
They're protesting about the right to vote

1439
01:46:30.790 --> 01:46:34.112
and the way they're treated in your state.

1440
01:46:34.230 --> 01:46:38.394
So that's your problem,
your responsibility,


1441
01:46:38.470 --> 01:46:40.472
and it's on your watch.

1442
01:46:41.150 --> 01:46:43.198
Mr. President, I disagree.

1443
01:46:43.830 --> 01:46:47.232
We have a certain way things are done.
It's the way it is.


1444
01:46:47.310 --> 01:46:49.472
And it's the way
the people want it to stay.


1445
01:46:51.630 --> 01:46:53.917
George, why are you doing this?

1446
01:46:53.990 --> 01:46:55.913
Your whole career
has been working for the poor.


1447
01:46:55.990 --> 01:46:57.674
Why are you off on this black thing?

1448
01:46:58.190 --> 01:47:00.841
Well, 'cause you can't ever satisfy them.

1449
01:47:01.910 --> 01:47:03.753
First, it's the front seat of the bus.

1450
01:47:03.830 --> 01:47:06.515
Next, it's take over the parks,

1451
01:47:06.590 --> 01:47:10.879
then it's the public schools,
then it's voting, then it's jobs,


1452
01:47:11.150 --> 01:47:14.359
then it's distribution of wealth
without work.


1453
01:47:17.030 --> 01:47:18.919
George, you seen
all those demonstrators


1454
01:47:18.990 --> 01:47:20.321
out front of the White House

1455
01:47:20.390 --> 01:47:22.597
keeping my Lady Bird awake
the whole damn night?


1456
01:47:22.670 --> 01:47:24.638
Oh, yes, Mr. President. I saw them.

1457
01:47:24.710 --> 01:47:27.600
Well, let's go out there, you and I,

1458
01:47:27.670 --> 01:47:31.311
and announce that you've decided to
let the blacks vote undeterred,


1459
01:47:31.750 --> 01:47:33.479
and this whole mess will go away.

1460
01:47:33.550 --> 01:47:36.520
And I don't have to draft bills
or force the issue.


1461
01:47:37.110 --> 01:47:39.795
Now, why don't we do that, George?

1462
01:47:39.870 --> 01:47:42.714
Why don't you just let the niggers vote?

1463
01:47:43.550 --> 01:47:45.712
You agree they got the right to vote,
don't you?


1464
01:47:45.790 --> 01:47:47.633
There's no quarrel with that.

1465
01:47:47.710 --> 01:47:49.792
I know that. That's the law.

1466
01:47:50.710 --> 01:47:52.553
Then why don't you just let 'em vote?

1467
01:47:52.950 --> 01:47:55.715
I don't have that power.
It belongs to the county registrars.


1468
01:47:55.790 --> 01:47:58.680
Now, don't shit me
about who runs Alabama.


1469
01:47:59.830 --> 01:48:01.480
I don't have any legal power

1470
01:48:01.550 --> 01:48:04.360
over the county registrars,
Mr. President.


1471
01:48:04.630 --> 01:48:06.712
They have their regulations
and they adhere.


1472
01:48:07.390 --> 01:48:10.200
Are you trying to shit me,
George Wallace?


1473
01:48:10.270 --> 01:48:12.557
Are you trying
to fuck over your President?


1474
01:48:12.630 --> 01:48:13.836
Mr. President...

1475
01:48:13.910 --> 01:48:16.151
We shouldn't even
be thinking about 1965.


1476
01:48:16.230 --> 01:48:18.961
We should be thinking about 1985.

1477
01:48:19.670 --> 01:48:21.798
You and I'll be
both dead and gone by then.


1478
01:48:22.950 --> 01:48:25.157
In 1985, what do you want looking back?

1479
01:48:25.230 --> 01:48:26.994
You want people
remembering you sayin',


1480
01:48:27.070 --> 01:48:31.519
"Wait," or "I can't," or, "It's too hard"?

1481
01:48:34.430 --> 01:48:37.434
I don't right care what they think,

1482
01:48:37.550 --> 01:48:39.917
and you shouldn't neither.

1483
01:48:44.750 --> 01:48:45.911
Well...

1484
01:48:47.350 --> 01:48:49.478
I'll be damned if I'm gonna let history

1485
01:48:49.550 --> 01:48:52.918
put me in the same place
as the likes of you.


1486
01:48:56.950 --> 01:49:00.033
<i>I speak tonight for the dignity of man</i>

1487
01:49:00.710 --> 01:49:03.793
<i>and the destiny of democracy.</i>

1488
01:49:04.670 --> 01:49:07.992
<i>At times, history and fate</i>

1489
01:49:08.070 --> 01:49:11.961
<i>meet at a single
time in a single place.</i>

1490
01:49:13.190 --> 01:49:18.117
<i>So it was last week in Selma, Alabama.</i>

1491
01:49:19.430 --> 01:49:22.434
<i>There, long suffering men and women</i>

1492
01:49:22.790 --> 01:49:28.399
<i>peacefully protested the denial
of their rights as Americans.</i>


1493
01:49:28.470 --> 01:49:30.632
<i>Rarely in any time</i>

1494
01:49:30.710 --> 01:49:34.112
<i>does an issue lay bare the secret heart</i>

1495
01:49:34.910 --> 01:49:36.878
<i>of America itself.</i>

1496
01:49:37.830 --> 01:49:42.392
<i>The issue for equal rights
for the American Negro</i>


1497
01:49:42.470 --> 01:49:44.313
<i>is that issue.</i>

1498
01:49:45.030 --> 01:49:46.156
<i>For this issue,</i>

1499
01:49:46.990 --> 01:49:50.676
<i>many of them were brutally assaulted.</i>

1500
01:49:54.510 --> 01:49:58.913
<i>There is no Negro problem.
There is no Southern problem.</i>


1501
01:49:59.670 --> 01:50:02.674
<i>There is only an American problem.</i>

1502
01:50:05.830 --> 01:50:08.674
<i>The Constitution says that</i>

1503
01:50:08.750 --> 01:50:12.311
<i>no person shall be kept from voting</i>

1504
01:50:12.390 --> 01:50:15.041
<i>because of his race or color.</i>

1505
01:50:16.270 --> 01:50:20.275
<i>To correct the denial
of this fundamental right,</i>


1506
01:50:20.350 --> 01:50:24.878
<i>this Wednesday,
I will send to Congress a law</i>


1507
01:50:24.950 --> 01:50:29.035
<i>designed to eliminate
these illegal barriers.</i>


1508
01:50:29.590 --> 01:50:31.991
<i>The bill will strike down</i>

1509
01:50:32.070 --> 01:50:35.836
<i>voting restrictions in all elections,</i>

1510
01:50:35.910 --> 01:50:39.631
<i>federal, state and local.</i>

1511
01:50:41.390 --> 01:50:43.358
<i>And we shall do this.</i>

1512
01:50:45.430 --> 01:50:48.718
<i>We shall overcome.</i>

1513
01:51:06.310 --> 01:51:08.472
We believe we can cover you
through Lowndes County,


1514
01:51:08.550 --> 01:51:12.157
but once we add the final day's march
through Montgomery,


1515
01:51:12.230 --> 01:51:14.881
and you're passing through
all those tall buildings and whatnot,


1516
01:51:14.950 --> 01:51:16.918
coverage becomes challenging.

1517
01:51:18.590 --> 01:51:20.991
So please consider

1518
01:51:22.150 --> 01:51:23.720
driving in on the final leg.

1519
01:51:23.790 --> 01:51:27.351
And please consider nixing
the speech at the Capitol.


1520
01:51:29.590 --> 01:51:31.752
Well, if Wallace will see us
when we arrive,


1521
01:51:31.830 --> 01:51:33.912
there'll be no need for a speech.

1522
01:51:35.190 --> 01:51:36.874
Can you arrange that?

1523
01:51:42.550 --> 01:51:43.961
I can't hide.

1524
01:51:45.590 --> 01:51:48.275
We can't hide. 
You understand.

1525
01:51:52.190 --> 01:51:54.841
I don't want to see
this go wrong for you.

1526
01:51:57.270 --> 01:51:59.637
Don't you want
to protect yourself, Doctor?


1527
01:52:01.390 --> 01:52:03.472
Let me try to do that.

1528
01:52:05.790 --> 01:52:07.554
You know, I know you
want to live to see

1529
01:52:07.630 --> 01:52:10.031
the fruits of all this work. 
I know you do.

1530
01:52:12.950 --> 01:52:16.750
I'm just asking you to allow us
to help you do that.


1531
01:52:24.470 --> 01:52:26.950
I'm no different than anybody else.

1532
01:52:28.990 --> 01:52:31.755
I want to live long and be happy.

1533
01:52:33.990 --> 01:52:37.312
But I'll not be focusing
on what I want today.


1534
01:52:38.990 --> 01:52:41.391
I'm focused on what God wants.

1535
01:52:44.670 --> 01:52:49.153
We're here for a reason,
through many, many storms.


1536
01:52:53.510 --> 01:52:57.231
But, today, the sun is shining,
and I'm about to stand in its warmth


1537
01:52:57.310 --> 01:53:01.713
alongside a lot of freedom-loving people
who worked hard to get us here.


1538
01:53:03.150 --> 01:53:07.200
I may not be with them
for all the sunny days to come,


1539
01:53:09.190 --> 01:53:12.194
but as long as there
is light ahead for them,


1540
01:53:14.190 --> 01:53:16.113
it's worth it to me.

1541
01:53:25.550 --> 01:53:27.200
Thank you, John.

1542
01:55:11.150 --> 01:55:15.394
<i>We heard them say
we'd never make it here.</i>


1543
01:55:17.310 --> 01:55:21.872
<i>We heard them say they'd stop us,
if it was the last thing they did.</i>


1544
01:55:23.870 --> 01:55:27.875
<i>We heard them say
we don't deserve to be here.</i>


1545
01:55:29.870 --> 01:55:33.920
<i>But today, we stand as Americans.</i>

1546
01:55:37.670 --> 01:55:39.240
<i>We are here,</i>

1547
01:55:40.110 --> 01:55:43.273
<i>and we ain't gonna let nobody
turn us around.</i>


1548
01:55:44.670 --> 01:55:47.241
<i>This mighty march,</i>

1549
01:55:48.070 --> 01:55:50.357
<i>which will be counted
as one of the greatest</i>


1550
01:55:50.430 --> 01:55:54.276
<i>demonstrations of protest and progress,</i>

1551
01:55:54.350 --> 01:55:57.991
<i>ends here in the Capitol of Alabama</i>

1552
01:55:58.070 --> 01:56:00.152
<i>for a vital purpose.</i>

1553
01:56:00.710 --> 01:56:04.954
<i>We have not fought only
for the right to sit where we please</i>


1554
01:56:05.030 --> 01:56:08.113
<i>and go to school where we please.</i>

1555
01:56:08.190 --> 01:56:12.400
<i>We do not only strive here today
to vote as we please.</i>


1556
01:56:13.550 --> 01:56:15.314
<i>But with our commitment,</i>

1557
01:56:15.390 --> 01:56:19.554
<i>we give birth each
day to a new energy</i>

1558
01:56:19.630 --> 01:56:23.191
<i>that is stronger than
our strongest opposition.</i>


1559
01:56:25.390 --> 01:56:28.758
<i>And we embrace
this new energy so boldly,</i>


1560
01:56:28.830 --> 01:56:31.276
<i>embody it so fervently,</i>

1561
01:56:31.350 --> 01:56:34.513
<i>that its reflection illuminates
a great darkness.</i>


1562
01:56:37.390 --> 01:56:40.678
<i>Our society has distorted who we are.</i>

1563
01:56:41.870 --> 01:56:44.521
<i>From slavery to the Reconstruction</i>

1564
01:56:44.950 --> 01:56:48.318
<i>to the precipice at which we now stand,</i>

1565
01:56:48.390 --> 01:56:54.193
<i>we have seen powerful
white men rule the world</i>


1566
01:56:54.630 --> 01:56:59.511
<i>while offering poor white men
a vicious lie as placation.</i>


1567
01:57:00.590 --> 01:57:03.514
<i>And when the poor white man's children</i>

1568
01:57:03.590 --> 01:57:07.072
<i>wail with a hunger
that cannot be satisfied,</i>


1569
01:57:07.670 --> 01:57:11.277
<i>he feeds them that same vicious lie.</i>

1570
01:57:12.390 --> 01:57:14.711
<i>A lie whispering to them</i>

1571
01:57:15.270 --> 01:57:17.591
<i>that regardless of their lot in life,</i>

1572
01:57:18.430 --> 01:57:22.116
<i>they can at least be triumphant
in the knowledge</i>


1573
01:57:22.190 --> 01:57:26.991
<i>that their whiteness makes
them superior to blackness.</i>


1574
01:57:27.470 --> 01:57:28.960
<i>But we know the truth.</i>

1575
01:57:30.350 --> 01:57:35.516
<i>We know the truth, and we will
go forward to that truth, to freedom.</i>


1576
01:57:38.630 --> 01:57:40.519
<i>We will not be stopped.</i>

1577
01:57:42.310 --> 01:57:43.880
<i>We will march for our rights.</i>

1578
01:57:44.590 --> 01:57:48.675
<i>We will march to demand
treatment as full citizens.</i>


1579
01:57:48.790 --> 01:57:52.476
<i>We will march until the viciousness
and the darkness</i>


1580
01:57:52.550 --> 01:57:55.918
<i>gives way to the light of righteousness.</i>

1581
01:57:56.470 --> 01:58:00.475
<i>No man, no myth,</i>

1582
01:58:00.670 --> 01:58:04.994
<i>no malaise will stop this movement.</i>

1583
01:58:05.070 --> 01:58:09.758
<i>We forbid it.
For we know that it is this darkness</i>


1584
01:58:09.830 --> 01:58:13.994
<i>that murders the best in us
and the best of us.</i>


1585
01:58:15.510 --> 01:58:19.310
<i>Whether Jimmie Lee Jackson
or James Reeb,</i>


1586
01:58:21.030 --> 01:58:24.352
<i>or four blameless little girls</i>

1587
01:58:24.590 --> 01:58:28.720
<i>struck down
before they had even begun.</i>


1588
01:58:30.350 --> 01:58:35.436
<i>You may ask, when will we
be free of this darkness?</i>


1589
01:58:35.510 --> 01:58:38.036
<i>I say to you today,
my brothers and sisters,</i>


1590
01:58:38.350 --> 01:58:41.672
<i>despite the pain, despite the tears,</i>

1591
01:58:41.790 --> 01:58:44.316
<i>our freedom will soon be upon us.</i>

1592
01:58:47.230 --> 01:58:51.519
<i>For "truth crushed to earth
will rise again."</i>


1593
01:58:54.230 --> 01:58:56.631
<i>When will we be free?</i>

1594
01:58:57.510 --> 01:58:59.877
<i>Soon, and very soon.</i>

1595
01:58:59.950 --> 01:59:03.238
<i>Because you shall reap what you sow.</i>

1596
01:59:07.150 --> 01:59:08.640
<i>When will we be free?</i>

1597
01:59:09.630 --> 01:59:11.792
<i>Soon, and very soon.</i>

1598
01:59:12.590 --> 01:59:15.480
<i>Because no lie can live forever.</i>

1599
01:59:19.230 --> 01:59:21.198
<i>When will we be free?</i>

1600
01:59:21.270 --> 01:59:23.591
<i>Soon, and very soon</i>

1601
01:59:23.670 --> 01:59:26.321
<i>because "Mine eyes have seen</i>

1602
01:59:26.390 --> 01:59:29.234
<i>"the glory of the coming of the Lord.</i>

1603
01:59:29.310 --> 01:59:31.472
<i>"He is trampling out the vintage</i>

1604
01:59:31.590 --> 01:59:33.911
<i>"where the grapes of wrath are stored.</i>

1605
01:59:33.990 --> 01:59:35.913
<i>"He hath loosed the fateful lightning</i>

1606
01:59:35.990 --> 01:59:38.152
<i>"of his terrible swift sword.</i>

1607
01:59:38.230 --> 01:59:40.358
<i>"His truth is marching on.</i>

1608
01:59:40.430 --> 01:59:46.995
<i>"Glory! Hallelujah!</i>

1609
01:59:47.070 --> 01:59:50.279
<i>"His truth is marching on."</i>